    \item We could use a rule that substitutes in just one place (a la Ariola).
   \item Rule \rulename{bind} fires only if the variable is equated to a
     \emph{value}, and values can freely be duplicated without duplicating
     work, so \rulename{bind} does not duplicate work.
   \end{itemize}
\item Rule \rulename{def-elim}. To achieve $\freevars{e} \disjoint \boundvars{h}$, use \rulename{subst}
  to substitute out the heap bindings.  This can only get stuck if $h$ has a variable introduction |x|,
  and |x| is mentioned in |e|.  It's fine to get stuck: Verse does not
  allow a \hexp{} to return an unbound logical variable.
